Content:
I agree.<p>At the very least, "variables" should be implemented with multistage processing like MetaLua or Template Haskell.  Really, I just want to say something like this:<p><pre><code>  foo = { background-color: #coffee; margin: 42; }

  bar.span { ,foo; something-else }
  baz.span { ,foo; something-else }
</code></pre>
I know I can do this with HTML (apply more classes), but I can envision cases where this is less hackish (or more natural, anyway).<p>Edit: the MetaOCaml people have some good reading about multistage programming: <a href="http://www.cs.rice.edu/~taha/MSP/" rel="nofollow">http://www.cs.rice.edu/~taha/MSP/</a>
